436 static ScheduleDAGInstrs * ----
437 createGCNMaxOccupancyMachineScheduler(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0
438 const GCNSubtarget &ST = C->MF->getSubtarget(); 0
439 ScheduleDAGMILive *DAG = ----
440 new GCNScheduleDAGMILive(C, std::make_unique(C)); 0
441 DAG->addMutation(createLoadClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
442 if (ST.shouldClusterStores()) 0
443 DAG->addMutation(createStoreClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
444 DAG->addMutation(createIGroupLPDAGMutation()); 0
445 DAG->addMutation(createAMDGPUMacroFusionDAGMutation()); 0
446 DAG->addMutation(createAMDGPUExportClusteringDAGMutation()); 0
447 return DAG; 0
448 } ----

459 createIterativeGCNMaxOccupancyMachineScheduler(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0
460 const GCNSubtarget &ST = C->MF->getSubtarget(); 0
461 auto DAG = new GCNIterativeScheduler(C, ----
462 GCNIterativeScheduler::SCHEDULE_LEGACYMAXOCCUPANCY); 0
463 DAG->addMutation(createLoadClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
464 if (ST.shouldClusterStores()) 0
465 DAG->addMutation(createStoreClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
466 return DAG; 0
467 } ----
468 ----
469 static ScheduleDAGInstrs *createMinRegScheduler(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0
470 return new GCNIterativeScheduler(C, ----
471 GCNIterativeScheduler::SCHEDULE_MINREGFORCED); 0
472 } ----
473 ----
474 static ScheduleDAGInstrs * ----
475 createIterativeILPMachineScheduler(MachineSchedContext *C) { 0
476 const GCNSubtarget &ST = C->MF->getSubtarget(); 0
477 auto DAG = new GCNIterativeScheduler(C, ----
478 GCNIterativeScheduler::SCHEDULE_ILP); 0
479 DAG->addMutation(createLoadClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
480 if (ST.shouldClusterStores()) 0
481 DAG->addMutation(createStoreClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
482 DAG->addMutation(createAMDGPUMacroFusionDAGMutation()); 0
483 return DAG; 0
484 } ----

513 ----
514 static StringRef computeDataLayout(const Triple &TT) { 0
515 if (TT.getArch() == Triple::r600) { 0
516 // 32-bit pointers. ----
517 return "e-p:32:32-i64:64-v16:16-v24:32-v32:32-v48:64-v96:128" ----
518 "-v192:256-v256:256-v512:512-v1024:1024-v2048:2048-n32:64-S32-A5-G1"; 0
519 } ----
520 ----
521 // 32-bit private, local, and region pointers. 64-bit global, constant and ----
522 // flat. 160-bit non-integral fat buffer pointers that include a 128-bit ----
523 // buffer descriptor and a 32-bit offset, which are indexed by 32-bit values ----
524 // (address space 7), and 128-bit non-integral buffer resourcees (address ----
525 // space 8) which cannot be non-trivilally accessed by LLVM memory operations ----
526 // like getelementptr. ----
527 return "e-p:64:64-p1:64:64-p2:32:32-p3:32:32-p4:64:64-p5:32:32-p6:32:32" ----
528 "-p7:160:256:256:32-p8:128:128-i64:64-v16:16-v24:32-v32:32-v48:64-v96:" ----
529 "128-v192:256-v256:256-v512:512-v1024:1024-v2048:2048-n32:64-S32-A5-" ----
530 "G1-ni:7:8"; 0
531 } ----
532 ----
533 LLVM_READNONE ----
534 static StringRef getGPUOrDefault(const Triple &TT, StringRef GPU) { 0
535 if (!GPU.empty()) 0
536 return GPU; 0
537 ----
538 // Need to default to a target with flat support for HSA. ----
539 if (TT.getArch() == Triple::amdgcn) 0
540 return TT.getOS() == Triple::AMDHSA ? "generic-hsa" : "generic"; 0
541 ----
542 return "r600"; 0
543 } ----
544 ----
545 static Reloc::Model getEffectiveRelocModel(std::optional RM) { 0
546 // The AMDGPU toolchain only supports generating shared objects, so we ----
547 // must always use PIC. ----
548 return Reloc::PIC_; 0
549 } ----

558 FS, Options, getEffectiveRelocModel(RM), ----

563 if (getMCSubtargetInfo()->checkFeatures("+wavefrontsize64")) 0
564 MRI.reset(llvm::createGCNMCRegisterInfo(AMDGPUDwarfFlavour::Wave64)); 0
565 else if (getMCSubtargetInfo()->checkFeatures("+wavefrontsize32")) 0
566 MRI.reset(llvm::createGCNMCRegisterInfo(AMDGPUDwarfFlavour::Wave32)); 0
567 } ----
568 } 0

588 /// Predicate for Internalize pass. ----
589 static bool mustPreserveGV(const GlobalValue &GV) { 0
590 if (const Function *F = dyn_cast(&GV)) 0
591 return F->isDeclaration() || F->getName().startswith("__asan_") || 0
592 F->getName().startswith("__sanitizer_") || 0
593 AMDGPU::isEntryFunctionCC(F->getCallingConv()); 0
594 ----
595 GV.removeDeadConstantUsers(); 0
596 return !GV.use_empty(); 0
597 } ----

602 ----
603 void AMDGPUTargetMachine::registerPassBuilderCallbacks(PassBuilder &PB) { 0
604 PB.registerPipelineParsingCallback( 0
605 [](StringRef PassName, ModulePassManager &PM, 0
606 ArrayRef) { ----
607 if (PassName == "amdgpu-unify-metadata") { 0
608 PM.addPass(AMDGPUUnifyMetadataPass()); 0
609 return true; 0
610 } ----
611 if (PassName == "amdgpu-printf-runtime-binding") { 0
612 PM.addPass(AMDGPUPrintfRuntimeBindingPass()); 0
613 return true; 0
614 } ----
615 if (PassName == "amdgpu-always-inline") { 0
616 PM.addPass(AMDGPUAlwaysInlinePass()); 0
617 return true; 0
618 } ----
619 if (PassName == "amdgpu-lower-module-lds") { 0
620 PM.addPass(AMDGPULowerModuleLDSPass()); 0
621 return true; 0
622 } ----
623 if (PassName == "amdgpu-lower-ctor-dtor") { 0
624 PM.addPass(AMDGPUCtorDtorLoweringPass()); 0
625 return true; 0
626 } ----
627 return false; 0
628 }); ----
629 PB.registerPipelineParsingCallback( 0
630 [this](StringRef PassName, FunctionPassManager &PM, 0
631 ArrayRef) { 0
632 if (PassName == "amdgpu-simplifylib") { 0
633 PM.addPass(AMDGPUSimplifyLibCallsPass(*this)); 0
634 return true; 0
635 } ----
636 if (PassName == "amdgpu-usenative") { 0
637 PM.addPass(AMDGPUUseNativeCallsPass()); 0
638 return true; 0
639 } ----
640 if (PassName == "amdgpu-promote-alloca") { 0
641 PM.addPass(AMDGPUPromoteAllocaPass(*this)); 0
642 return true; 0
643 } ----
644 if (PassName == "amdgpu-promote-alloca-to-vector") { 0
645 PM.addPass(AMDGPUPromoteAllocaToVectorPass(*this)); 0
646 return true; 0
647 } ----
648 if (PassName == "amdgpu-lower-kernel-attributes") { 0
649 PM.addPass(AMDGPULowerKernelAttributesPass()); 0
650 return true; 0
651 } ----
652 if (PassName == "amdgpu-promote-kernel-arguments") { 0
653 PM.addPass(AMDGPUPromoteKernelArgumentsPass()); 0
654 return true; 0
655 } ----
656 if (PassName == "amdgpu-unify-divergent-exit-nodes") { 0
657 PM.addPass(AMDGPUUnifyDivergentExitNodesPass()); 0
658 return true; 0
659 } ----
660 if (PassName == "amdgpu-atomic-optimizer") { 0
661 PM.addPass( 0
662 AMDGPUAtomicOptimizerPass(*this, AMDGPUAtomicOptimizerStrategy)); 0
663 return true; 0
664 } ----
665 if (PassName == "amdgpu-codegenprepare") { 0
666 PM.addPass(AMDGPUCodeGenPreparePass(*this)); 0
667 return true; 0
668 } ----
669 return false; 0
670 }); ----
671 ----
672 PB.registerAnalysisRegistrationCallback([](FunctionAnalysisManager &FAM) { 0
673 FAM.registerPass([&] { return AMDGPUAA(); }); 0
674 }); 0
675 ----
676 PB.registerParseAACallback([](StringRef AAName, AAManager &AAM) { 0
677 if (AAName == "amdgpu-aa") { 0
678 AAM.registerFunctionAnalysis(); 0
679 return true; 0
680 } ----
681 return false; 0
682 }); ----
683 ----
684 PB.registerPipelineStartEPCallback( 0
685 [this](ModulePassManager &PM, OptimizationLevel Level) { 0
686 FunctionPassManager FPM; 0
687 FPM.addPass(AMDGPUUseNativeCallsPass()); 0
688 if (EnableLibCallSimplify && Level != OptimizationLevel::O0) 0
689 FPM.addPass(AMDGPUSimplifyLibCallsPass(*this)); 0
690 PM.addPass(createModuleToFunctionPassAdaptor(std::move(FPM))); 0
691 }); 0
692 ----
693 PB.registerPipelineEarlySimplificationEPCallback( 0
694 [](ModulePassManager &PM, OptimizationLevel Level) { 0
695 PM.addPass(AMDGPUPrintfRuntimeBindingPass()); 0
696 ----
697 if (Level == OptimizationLevel::O0) 0
698 return; 0
699 ----
700 PM.addPass(AMDGPUUnifyMetadataPass()); 0
701 ----
702 if (InternalizeSymbols) { 0
703 PM.addPass(InternalizePass(mustPreserveGV)); 0
704 PM.addPass(GlobalDCEPass()); 0
705 } ----
706 ----
707 if (EarlyInlineAll && !EnableFunctionCalls) 0
708 PM.addPass(AMDGPUAlwaysInlinePass()); 0
709 }); ----
710 ----
711 PB.registerCGSCCOptimizerLateEPCallback( 0
712 [this](CGSCCPassManager &PM, OptimizationLevel Level) { 0
713 if (Level == OptimizationLevel::O0) 0
714 return; 0
715 ----
716 FunctionPassManager FPM; 0
717 ----
718 // Add promote kernel arguments pass to the opt pipeline right before ----
719 // infer address spaces which is needed to do actual address space ----
720 // rewriting. ----
721 if (Level.getSpeedupLevel() > OptimizationLevel::O1.getSpeedupLevel() && 0
722 EnablePromoteKernelArguments) 0
723 FPM.addPass(AMDGPUPromoteKernelArgumentsPass()); 0
724 ----
725 // Add infer address spaces pass to the opt pipeline after inlining ----
726 // but before SROA to increase SROA opportunities. ----
727 FPM.addPass(InferAddressSpacesPass()); 0
728 ----
729 // This should run after inlining to have any chance of doing ----
730 // anything, and before other cleanup optimizations. ----
731 FPM.addPass(AMDGPULowerKernelAttributesPass()); 0
732 ----
733 if (Level != OptimizationLevel::O0) { 0
734 // Promote alloca to vector before SROA and loop unroll. If we ----
735 // manage to eliminate allocas before unroll we may choose to unroll ----
736 // less. ----
737 FPM.addPass(AMDGPUPromoteAllocaToVectorPass(*this)); 0
738 } ----
739 ----
740 PM.addPass(createCGSCCToFunctionPassAdaptor(std::move(FPM))); 0
741 }); 0
742 } 0

744 int64_t AMDGPUTargetMachine::getNullPointerValue(unsigned AddrSpace) { 0
745 return (AddrSpace == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS || 0
746 AddrSpace == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS || 0
747 AddrSpace == AMDGPUAS::REGION_ADDRESS) ----
748 ? -1 0
749 : 0; 0
750 } ----
751 ----
752 bool AMDGPUTargetMachine::isNoopAddrSpaceCast(unsigned SrcAS, 0
753 unsigned DestAS) const { ----
754 return AMDGPU::isFlatGlobalAddrSpace(SrcAS) && 0
755 AMDGPU::isFlatGlobalAddrSpace(DestAS); 0
756 } ----
757 ----
758 unsigned AMDGPUTargetMachine::getAssumedAddrSpace(const Value *V) const { 0
759 const auto *LD = dyn_cast(V); 0
760 if (!LD) 0
761 return AMDGPUAS::UNKNOWN_ADDRESS_SPACE; 0
762 ----
763 // It must be a generic pointer loaded. ----
764 assert(V->getType()->isPointerTy() && 0
765 V->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS); ----
766 ----
767 const auto *Ptr = LD->getPointerOperand(); 0
768 if (Ptr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() != AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS) 0
769 return AMDGPUAS::UNKNOWN_ADDRESS_SPACE; 0
770 // For a generic pointer loaded from the constant memory, it could be assumed ----
771 // as a global pointer since the constant memory is only populated on the ----
772 // host side. As implied by the offload programming model, only global ----
773 // pointers could be referenced on the host side. ----
774 return AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS; 0
775 } ----
776 ----
777 std::pair ----
778 AMDGPUTargetMachine::getPredicatedAddrSpace(const Value *V) const { 0
779 if (auto *II = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
780 switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) { 0
781 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_is_shared: 0
782 return std::pair(II->getArgOperand(0), AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS); 0
783 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_is_private: 0
784 return std::pair(II->getArgOperand(0), AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS); 0
785 default: 0
786 break; 0
787 } ----
788 return std::pair(nullptr, -1); 0
789 } ----
790 // Check the global pointer predication based on ----
791 // (!is_share(p) && !is_private(p)). Note that logic 'and' is commutative and ----
792 // the order of 'is_shared' and 'is_private' is not significant. ----
793 Value *Ptr; ----
794 if (match( 0
795 const_cast(V), ----
796 m_c_And(m_Not(m_Intrinsic(m_Value(Ptr))), 0
797 m_Not(m_Intrinsic( 0
798 m_Deferred(Ptr)))))) 0
799 return std::pair(Ptr, AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS); 0
800 ----
801 return std::pair(nullptr, -1); 0
802 } ----
803 ----
804 unsigned ----
805 AMDGPUTargetMachine::getAddressSpaceForPseudoSourceKind(unsigned Kind) const { 0
806 switch (Kind) { 0
807 case PseudoSourceValue::Stack: 0
808 case PseudoSourceValue::FixedStack: ----
809 return AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS; 0
810 case PseudoSourceValue::ConstantPool: 0
811 case PseudoSourceValue::GOT: ----
812 case PseudoSourceValue::JumpTable: ----
813 case PseudoSourceValue::GlobalValueCallEntry: ----
814 case PseudoSourceValue::ExternalSymbolCallEntry: ----
815 return AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS; 0
816 } ----
817 return AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS; 0
818 } ----

824 GCNTargetMachine::GCNTargetMachine(const Target &T, const Triple &TT, 0
825 StringRef CPU, StringRef FS, ----
826 TargetOptions Options, ----
827 std::optional RM, ----
828 std::optional CM, ----
829 CodeGenOpt::Level OL, bool JIT) ----
830 : AMDGPUTargetMachine(T, TT, CPU, FS, Options, RM, CM, OL) {} 0
831 ----
832 const TargetSubtargetInfo * ----
833 GCNTargetMachine::getSubtargetImpl(const Function &F) const { 0
834 StringRef GPU = getGPUName(F); 0
835 StringRef FS = getFeatureString(F); 0
836 ----
837 SmallString<128> SubtargetKey(GPU); 0
838 SubtargetKey.append(FS); 0
839 ----
840 auto &I = SubtargetMap[SubtargetKey]; 0
841 if (!I) { 0
842 // This needs to be done before we create a new subtarget since any ----
843 // creation will depend on the TM and the code generation flags on the ----
844 // function that reside in TargetOptions. ----
845 resetTargetOptions(F); 0
846 I = std::make_unique(TargetTriple, GPU, FS, *this); 0
847 } ----
848 ----
849 I->setScalarizeGlobalBehavior(ScalarizeGlobal); 0
850 ----
851 return I.get(); 0
852 } 0

856 return TargetTransformInfo(GCNTTIImpl(this, F)); 0
857 } ----

887 ScheduleDAGInstrs * ----
888 createPostMachineScheduler(MachineSchedContext *C) const override { 0
889 ScheduleDAGMI *DAG = new GCNPostScheduleDAGMILive( ----
890 C, std::make_unique(C), 0
891 /*RemoveKillFlags=*/true); 0
892 const GCNSubtarget &ST = C->MF->getSubtarget(); 0
893 DAG->addMutation(createLoadClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
894 if (ST.shouldClusterStores()) 0
895 DAG->addMutation(createStoreClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
896 DAG->addMutation(ST.createFillMFMAShadowMutation(DAG->TII)); 0
897 DAG->addMutation(createIGroupLPDAGMutation()); 0
898 if (isPassEnabled(EnableVOPD, CodeGenOpt::Less)) 0
899 DAG->addMutation(createVOPDPairingMutation()); 0
900 return DAG; 0
901 } ----

933 AMDGPUPassConfig::AMDGPUPassConfig(LLVMTargetMachine &TM, PassManagerBase &PM) 0
934 : TargetPassConfig(TM, PM) { 0
935 // Exceptions and StackMaps are not supported, so these passes will never do ----
936 // anything. ----
937 disablePass(&StackMapLivenessID); 0
938 disablePass(&FuncletLayoutID); 0
939 // Garbage collection is not supported. ----
940 disablePass(&GCLoweringID); 0
941 disablePass(&ShadowStackGCLoweringID); 0
942 } 0
943 ----
944 void AMDGPUPassConfig::addEarlyCSEOrGVNPass() { 0
945 if (getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::Aggressive) 0
946 addPass(createGVNPass()); 0
947 else ----
948 addPass(createEarlyCSEPass()); 0
949 } 0
950 ----
951 void AMDGPUPassConfig::addStraightLineScalarOptimizationPasses() { 0
952 addPass(createSeparateConstOffsetFromGEPPass()); 0
953 // ReassociateGEPs exposes more opportunities for SLSR. See ----
954 // the example in reassociate-geps-and-slsr.ll. ----
955 addPass(createStraightLineStrengthReducePass()); 0
956 // SeparateConstOffsetFromGEP and SLSR creates common expressions which GVN or ----
957 // EarlyCSE can reuse. ----
958 addEarlyCSEOrGVNPass(); 0
959 // Run NaryReassociate after EarlyCSE/GVN to be more effective. ----
960 addPass(createNaryReassociatePass()); 0
961 // NaryReassociate on GEPs creates redundant common expressions, so run ----
962 // EarlyCSE after it. ----
963 addPass(createEarlyCSEPass()); 0
964 } 0
965 ----
966 void AMDGPUPassConfig::addIRPasses() { 0
967 const AMDGPUTargetMachine &TM = getAMDGPUTargetMachine(); 0
968 ----
969 // There is no reason to run these. ----
970 disablePass(&StackMapLivenessID); 0
971 disablePass(&FuncletLayoutID); 0
972 disablePass(&PatchableFunctionID); 0
973 ----
974 addPass(createAMDGPUPrintfRuntimeBinding()); 0
975 if (LowerCtorDtor) 0
976 addPass(createAMDGPUCtorDtorLoweringLegacyPass()); 0
977 ----
978 // Function calls are not supported, so make sure we inline everything. ----
979 addPass(createAMDGPUAlwaysInlinePass()); 0
980 addPass(createAlwaysInlinerLegacyPass()); 0
981 ----
982 // Handle uses of OpenCL image2d_t, image3d_t and sampler_t arguments. ----
983 if (TM.getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::r600) 0
984 addPass(createR600OpenCLImageTypeLoweringPass()); 0
985 ----
986 // Replace OpenCL enqueued block function pointers with global variables. ----
987 addPass(createAMDGPUOpenCLEnqueuedBlockLoweringPass()); 0
988 ----
989 // Runs before PromoteAlloca so the latter can account for function uses ----
990 if (EnableLowerModuleLDS) { 0
991 addPass(createAMDGPULowerModuleLDSPass()); 0
992 } ----
993 ----
994 // AMDGPUAttributor infers lack of llvm.amdgcn.lds.kernel.id calls, so run ----
995 // after their introduction ----
996 if (TM.getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
997 addPass(createAMDGPUAttributorPass()); 0
998 ----
999 if (TM.getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1000 addPass(createInferAddressSpacesPass()); 0
1001 ----
1002 addPass(createAtomicExpandPass()); 0
1003 ----
1004 if (TM.getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) { 0
1005 addPass(createAMDGPUPromoteAlloca()); 0
1006 ----
1007 if (EnableSROA) 0
1008 addPass(createSROAPass()); 0
1009 if (isPassEnabled(EnableScalarIRPasses)) 0
1010 addStraightLineScalarOptimizationPasses(); 0
1011 ----
1012 if (EnableAMDGPUAliasAnalysis) { 0
1013 addPass(createAMDGPUAAWrapperPass()); 0
1014 addPass(createExternalAAWrapperPass([](Pass &P, Function &, 0
1015 AAResults &AAR) { ----
1016 if (auto *WrapperPass = P.getAnalysisIfAvailable()) 0
1017 AAR.addAAResult(WrapperPass->getResult()); 0
1018 })); 0
1019 } ----
1020 ----
1021 if (TM.getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::amdgcn) { 0
1022 // TODO: May want to move later or split into an early and late one. ----
1023 addPass(createAMDGPUCodeGenPreparePass()); 0
1024 } ----
1025 ----
1026 // Try to hoist loop invariant parts of divisions AMDGPUCodeGenPrepare may ----
1027 // have expanded. ----
1028 if (TM.getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::Less) 0
1029 addPass(createLICMPass()); 0
1030 } ----
1031 ----
1032 TargetPassConfig::addIRPasses(); 0
1033 ----
1034 // EarlyCSE is not always strong enough to clean up what LSR produces. For ----
1035 // example, GVN can combine ----
1036 // ----
1037 // %0 = add %a, %b ----
1038 // %1 = add %b, %a ----
1039 // ----
1040 // and ----
1041 // ----
1042 // %0 = shl nsw %a, 2 ----
1043 // %1 = shl %a, 2 ----
1044 // ----
1045 // but EarlyCSE can do neither of them. ----
1046 if (isPassEnabled(EnableScalarIRPasses)) 0
1047 addEarlyCSEOrGVNPass(); 0
1048 } 0
1049 ----
1050 void AMDGPUPassConfig::addCodeGenPrepare() { 0
1051 if (TM->getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::amdgcn) { 0
1052 if (RemoveIncompatibleFunctions) 0
1053 addPass(createAMDGPURemoveIncompatibleFunctionsPass(TM)); 0
1054 ----
1055 // FIXME: This pass adds 2 hacky attributes that can be replaced with an ----
1056 // analysis, and should be removed. ----
1057 addPass(createAMDGPUAnnotateKernelFeaturesPass()); 0
1058 } ----
1059 ----
1060 if (TM->getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::amdgcn && 0
1061 EnableLowerKernelArguments) 0
1062 addPass(createAMDGPULowerKernelArgumentsPass()); 0
1063 ----
1064 TargetPassConfig::addCodeGenPrepare(); 0
1065 ----
1066 if (isPassEnabled(EnableLoadStoreVectorizer)) 0
1067 addPass(createLoadStoreVectorizerPass()); 0
1068 ----
1069 // LowerSwitch pass may introduce unreachable blocks that can ----
1070 // cause unexpected behavior for subsequent passes. Placing it ----
1071 // here seems better that these blocks would get cleaned up by ----
1072 // UnreachableBlockElim inserted next in the pass flow. ----
1073 addPass(createLowerSwitchPass()); 0
1074 } 0
1075 ----
1076 bool AMDGPUPassConfig::addPreISel() { 0
1077 if (TM->getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1078 addPass(createFlattenCFGPass()); 0
1079 return false; 0
1080 } ----
1081 ----
1082 bool AMDGPUPassConfig::addInstSelector() { 0
1083 addPass(createAMDGPUISelDag(getAMDGPUTargetMachine(), getOptLevel())); 0
1084 return false; 0
1085 } ----
1086 ----
1087 bool AMDGPUPassConfig::addGCPasses() { 0
1088 // Do nothing. GC is not supported. ----
1089 return false; 0
1090 } ----
1091 ----
1092 llvm::ScheduleDAGInstrs * ----
1093 AMDGPUPassConfig::createMachineScheduler(MachineSchedContext *C) const { 0
1094 const GCNSubtarget &ST = C->MF->getSubtarget(); 0
1095 ScheduleDAGMILive *DAG = createGenericSchedLive(C); 0
1096 DAG->addMutation(createLoadClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
1097 if (ST.shouldClusterStores()) 0
1098 DAG->addMutation(createStoreClusterDAGMutation(DAG->TII, DAG->TRI)); 0
1099 return DAG; 0
1100 } ----

1112 ----
1113 ScheduleDAGInstrs *GCNPassConfig::createMachineScheduler( 0
1114 MachineSchedContext *C) const { ----
1115 const GCNSubtarget &ST = C->MF->getSubtarget(); 0
1116 if (ST.enableSIScheduler()) 0
1117 return createSIMachineScheduler(C); 0
1118 ----
1119 if (EnableMaxIlpSchedStrategy) 0
1120 return createGCNMaxILPMachineScheduler(C); 0
1121 ----
1122 return createGCNMaxOccupancyMachineScheduler(C); 0
1123 } ----
1124 ----
1125 bool GCNPassConfig::addPreISel() { 0
1126 AMDGPUPassConfig::addPreISel(); 0
1127 ----
1128 if (TM->getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1129 addPass(createAMDGPULateCodeGenPreparePass()); 0
1130 ----
1131 if ((TM->getOptLevel() >= CodeGenOpt::Less) && 0
1132 (AMDGPUAtomicOptimizerStrategy != ScanOptions::None)) { 0
1133 addPass(createAMDGPUAtomicOptimizerPass(AMDGPUAtomicOptimizerStrategy)); 0
1134 } ----
1135 ----
1136 if (TM->getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1137 addPass(createSinkingPass()); 0
1138 ----
1139 // Merge divergent exit nodes. StructurizeCFG won't recognize the multi-exit ----
1140 // regions formed by them. ----
1141 addPass(&AMDGPUUnifyDivergentExitNodesID); 0
1142 if (!LateCFGStructurize) { 0
1143 if (EnableStructurizerWorkarounds) { 0
1144 addPass(createFixIrreduciblePass()); 0
1145 addPass(createUnifyLoopExitsPass()); 0
1146 } ----
1147 addPass(createStructurizeCFGPass(false)); // true -> SkipUniformRegions 0
1148 } ----
1149 addPass(createAMDGPUAnnotateUniformValues()); 0
1150 if (!LateCFGStructurize) { 0
1151 addPass(createSIAnnotateControlFlowPass()); 0
1152 // TODO: Move this right after structurizeCFG to avoid extra divergence ----
1153 // analysis. This depends on stopping SIAnnotateControlFlow from making ----
1154 // control flow modifications. ----
1155 addPass(createAMDGPURewriteUndefForPHIPass()); 0
1156 } ----
1157 addPass(createLCSSAPass()); 0
1158 ----
1159 if (TM->getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::Less) 0
1160 addPass(&AMDGPUPerfHintAnalysisID); 0
1161 ----
1162 return false; 0
1163 } ----
1164 ----
1165 void GCNPassConfig::addMachineSSAOptimization() { 0
1166 TargetPassConfig::addMachineSSAOptimization(); 0
1167 ----
1168 // We want to fold operands after PeepholeOptimizer has run (or as part of ----
1169 // it), because it will eliminate extra copies making it easier to fold the ----
1170 // real source operand. We want to eliminate dead instructions after, so that ----
1171 // we see fewer uses of the copies. We then need to clean up the dead ----
1172 // instructions leftover after the operands are folded as well. ----
1173 // ----
1174 // XXX - Can we get away without running DeadMachineInstructionElim again? ----
1175 addPass(&SIFoldOperandsID); 0
1176 if (EnableDPPCombine) 0
1177 addPass(&GCNDPPCombineID); 0
1178 addPass(&SILoadStoreOptimizerID); 0
1179 if (isPassEnabled(EnableSDWAPeephole)) { 0
1180 addPass(&SIPeepholeSDWAID); 0
1181 addPass(&EarlyMachineLICMID); 0
1182 addPass(&MachineCSEID); 0
1183 addPass(&SIFoldOperandsID); 0
1184 } ----
1185 addPass(&DeadMachineInstructionElimID); 0
1186 addPass(createSIShrinkInstructionsPass()); 0
1187 } 0

1190 if (EnableEarlyIfConversion) 0
1191 addPass(&EarlyIfConverterID); 0
1192 ----
1193 TargetPassConfig::addILPOpts(); 0
1194 return false; 0
1195 } ----

1245 ----
1246 void GCNPassConfig::addFastRegAlloc() { 0
1247 // FIXME: We have to disable the verifier here because of PHIElimination + ----
1248 // TwoAddressInstructions disabling it. ----
1249 ----
1250 // This must be run immediately after phi elimination and before ----
1251 // TwoAddressInstructions, otherwise the processing of the tied operand of ----
1252 // SI_ELSE will introduce a copy of the tied operand source after the else. ----
1253 insertPass(&PHIEliminationID, &SILowerControlFlowID); 0
1254 ----
1255 insertPass(&TwoAddressInstructionPassID, &SIWholeQuadModeID); 0
1256 insertPass(&TwoAddressInstructionPassID, &SIPreAllocateWWMRegsID); 0
1257 ----
1258 TargetPassConfig::addFastRegAlloc(); 0
1259 } 0
1260 ----
1261 void GCNPassConfig::addOptimizedRegAlloc() { 0
1262 // Allow the scheduler to run before SIWholeQuadMode inserts exec manipulation ----
1263 // instructions that cause scheduling barriers. ----
1264 insertPass(&MachineSchedulerID, &SIWholeQuadModeID); 0
1265 insertPass(&MachineSchedulerID, &SIPreAllocateWWMRegsID); 0
1266 ----
1267 if (OptExecMaskPreRA) 0
1268 insertPass(&MachineSchedulerID, &SIOptimizeExecMaskingPreRAID); 0
1269 ----
1270 if (EnableRewritePartialRegUses) 0
1271 insertPass(&RenameIndependentSubregsID, &GCNRewritePartialRegUsesID); 0
1272 ----
1273 if (isPassEnabled(EnablePreRAOptimizations)) 0
1274 insertPass(&RenameIndependentSubregsID, &GCNPreRAOptimizationsID); 0
1275 ----
1276 // This is not an essential optimization and it has a noticeable impact on ----
1277 // compilation time, so we only enable it from O2. ----
1278 if (TM->getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::Less) 0
1279 insertPass(&MachineSchedulerID, &SIFormMemoryClausesID); 0
1280 ----
1281 // FIXME: when an instruction has a Killed operand, and the instruction is ----
1282 // inside a bundle, seems only the BUNDLE instruction appears as the Kills of ----
1283 // the register in LiveVariables, this would trigger a failure in verifier, ----
1284 // we should fix it and enable the verifier. ----
1285 if (OptVGPRLiveRange) 0
1286 insertPass(&LiveVariablesID, &SIOptimizeVGPRLiveRangeID); 0
1287 // This must be run immediately after phi elimination and before ----
1288 // TwoAddressInstructions, otherwise the processing of the tied operand of ----
1289 // SI_ELSE will introduce a copy of the tied operand source after the else. ----
1290 insertPass(&PHIEliminationID, &SILowerControlFlowID); 0
1291 ----
1292 if (EnableDCEInRA) 0
1293 insertPass(&DetectDeadLanesID, &DeadMachineInstructionElimID); 0
1294 ----
1295 TargetPassConfig::addOptimizedRegAlloc(); 0
1296 } 0

1299 if (EnableRegReassign) 0
1300 addPass(&GCNNSAReassignID); 0
1301 return true; 0
1302 } ----
1303 ----
1304 FunctionPass *GCNPassConfig::createSGPRAllocPass(bool Optimized) { 0
1305 // Initialize the global default. ----
1306 llvm::call_once(InitializeDefaultSGPRRegisterAllocatorFlag, 0
1307 initializeDefaultSGPRRegisterAllocatorOnce); ----
1308 ----
1309 RegisterRegAlloc::FunctionPassCtor Ctor = SGPRRegisterRegAlloc::getDefault(); 0
1310 if (Ctor != useDefaultRegisterAllocator) 0
1311 return Ctor(); 0
1312 ----
1313 if (Optimized) 0
1314 return createGreedyRegisterAllocator(onlyAllocateSGPRs); 0
1315 ----
1316 return createFastRegisterAllocator(onlyAllocateSGPRs, false); 0
1317 } ----
1318 ----
1319 FunctionPass *GCNPassConfig::createVGPRAllocPass(bool Optimized) { 0
1320 // Initialize the global default. ----
1321 llvm::call_once(InitializeDefaultVGPRRegisterAllocatorFlag, 0
1322 initializeDefaultVGPRRegisterAllocatorOnce); ----
1323 ----
1324 RegisterRegAlloc::FunctionPassCtor Ctor = VGPRRegisterRegAlloc::getDefault(); 0
1325 if (Ctor != useDefaultRegisterAllocator) 0
1326 return Ctor(); 0
1327 ----
1328 if (Optimized) 0
1329 return createGreedyVGPRRegisterAllocator(); 0
1330 ----
1331 return createFastVGPRRegisterAllocator(); 0
1332 } ----
1333 ----
1334 FunctionPass *GCNPassConfig::createRegAllocPass(bool Optimized) { 0
1335 llvm_unreachable("should not be used"); 0
1336 } ----
1337 ----
1338 static const char RegAllocOptNotSupportedMessage[] = ----
1339 "-regalloc not supported with amdgcn. Use -sgpr-regalloc and -vgpr-regalloc"; ----
1340 ----
1341 bool GCNPassConfig::addRegAssignAndRewriteFast() { 0
1342 if (!usingDefaultRegAlloc()) 0
1343 report_fatal_error(RegAllocOptNotSupportedMessage); 0
1344 ----
1345 addPass(&GCNPreRALongBranchRegID); 0
1346 ----
1347 addPass(createSGPRAllocPass(false)); 0
1348 ----
1349 // Equivalent of PEI for SGPRs. ----
1350 addPass(&SILowerSGPRSpillsID); 0
1351 ----
1352 addPass(createVGPRAllocPass(false)); 0
1353 return true; 0
1354 } ----
1355 ----
1356 bool GCNPassConfig::addRegAssignAndRewriteOptimized() { 0
1357 if (!usingDefaultRegAlloc()) 0
1358 report_fatal_error(RegAllocOptNotSupportedMessage); 0
1359 ----
1360 addPass(&GCNPreRALongBranchRegID); 0
1361 ----
1362 addPass(createSGPRAllocPass(true)); 0
1363 ----
1364 // Commit allocated register changes. This is mostly necessary because too ----
1365 // many things rely on the use lists of the physical registers, such as the ----
1366 // verifier. This is only necessary with allocators which use LiveIntervals, ----
1367 // since FastRegAlloc does the replacements itself. ----
1368 addPass(createVirtRegRewriter(false)); 0
1369 ----
1370 // Equivalent of PEI for SGPRs. ----
1371 addPass(&SILowerSGPRSpillsID); 0
1372 ----
1373 addPass(createVGPRAllocPass(true)); 0
1374 ----
1375 addPreRewrite(); 0
1376 addPass(&VirtRegRewriterID); 0
1377 ----
1378 return true; 0
1379 } ----

1385 TargetPassConfig::addPostRegAlloc(); 0
1386 } 0

1388 void GCNPassConfig::addPreSched2() { 0

1392 } 0
1393 ----
1394 void GCNPassConfig::addPreEmitPass() { 0
1395 if (isPassEnabled(EnableVOPD, CodeGenOpt::Less)) 0
1396 addPass(&GCNCreateVOPDID); 0
1397 addPass(createSIMemoryLegalizerPass()); 0
1398 addPass(createSIInsertWaitcntsPass()); 0
1399 ----
1400 addPass(createSIModeRegisterPass()); 0
1401 ----
1402 if (getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1403 addPass(&SIInsertHardClausesID); 0
1404 ----
1405 addPass(&SILateBranchLoweringPassID); 0
1406 if (isPassEnabled(EnableSetWavePriority, CodeGenOpt::Less)) 0
1407 addPass(createAMDGPUSetWavePriorityPass()); 0
1408 if (getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1409 addPass(&SIPreEmitPeepholeID); 0
1410 // The hazard recognizer that runs as part of the post-ra scheduler does not ----
1411 // guarantee to be able handle all hazards correctly. This is because if there ----
1412 // are multiple scheduling regions in a basic block, the regions are scheduled ----
1413 // bottom up, so when we begin to schedule a region we don't know what ----
1414 // instructions were emitted directly before it. ----
1415 // ----
1416 // Here we add a stand-alone hazard recognizer pass which can handle all ----
1417 // cases. ----
1418 addPass(&PostRAHazardRecognizerID); 0
1419 ----
1420 if (isPassEnabled(EnableInsertDelayAlu, CodeGenOpt::Less)) 0
1421 addPass(&AMDGPUInsertDelayAluID); 0
1422 ----
1423 addPass(&BranchRelaxationPassID); 0
1424 } 0

1453 ----
1454 bool GCNTargetMachine::parseMachineFunctionInfo( 0
1455 const yaml::MachineFunctionInfo &MFI_, PerFunctionMIParsingState &PFS, ----
1456 SMDiagnostic &Error, SMRange &SourceRange) const { ----
1457 const yaml::SIMachineFunctionInfo &YamlMFI = 0
1458 static_cast(MFI_); ----
1459 MachineFunction &MF = PFS.MF; 0
1460 SIMachineFunctionInfo *MFI = MF.getInfo(); 0
1461 ----
1462 if (MFI->initializeBaseYamlFields(YamlMFI, MF, PFS, Error, SourceRange)) 0
1463 return true; 0
1464 ----
1465 if (MFI->Occupancy == 0) { 0
1466 // Fixup the subtarget dependent default value. ----
1467 const GCNSubtarget &ST = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
1468 MFI->Occupancy = ST.computeOccupancy(MF.getFunction(), MFI->getLDSSize()); 0
1469 } ----
1470 ----
1471 auto parseRegister = [&](const yaml::StringValue &RegName, Register &RegVal) { 0
1472 Register TempReg; 0
1473 if (parseNamedRegisterReference(PFS, TempReg, RegName.Value, Error)) { 0
1474 SourceRange = RegName.SourceRange; 0
1475 return true; 0
1476 } ----
1477 RegVal = TempReg; 0
1478 ----
1479 return false; 0
1480 }; 0
1481 ----
1482 auto parseOptionalRegister = [&](const yaml::StringValue &RegName, 0
1483 Register &RegVal) { ----
1484 return !RegName.Value.empty() && parseRegister(RegName, RegVal); 0
1485 }; 0
1486 ----
1487 if (parseOptionalRegister(YamlMFI.VGPRForAGPRCopy, MFI->VGPRForAGPRCopy)) 0
1488 return true; 0
1489 ----
1490 if (parseOptionalRegister(YamlMFI.SGPRForEXECCopy, MFI->SGPRForEXECCopy)) 0
1491 return true; 0
1492 ----
1493 if (parseOptionalRegister(YamlMFI.LongBranchReservedReg, 0
1494 MFI->LongBranchReservedReg)) 0
1495 return true; 0
1496 ----
1497 auto diagnoseRegisterClass = [&](const yaml::StringValue &RegName) { 0
1498 // Create a diagnostic for a the register string literal. ----
1499 const MemoryBuffer &Buffer = ----
1500 *PFS.SM->getMemoryBuffer(PFS.SM->getMainFileID()); 0
1501 Error = SMDiagnostic(*PFS.SM, SMLoc(), Buffer.getBufferIdentifier(), 1, 0
1502 RegName.Value.size(), SourceMgr::DK_Error, 0
1503 "incorrect register class for field", RegName.Value, 0
1504 std::nullopt, std::nullopt); 0
1505 SourceRange = RegName.SourceRange; 0
1506 return true; 0
1507 }; 0
1508 ----
1509 if (parseRegister(YamlMFI.ScratchRSrcReg, MFI->ScratchRSrcReg) || 0
1510 parseRegister(YamlMFI.FrameOffsetReg, MFI->FrameOffsetReg) || 0
1511 parseRegister(YamlMFI.StackPtrOffsetReg, MFI->StackPtrOffsetReg)) 0
1512 return true; 0
1513 ----
1514 if (MFI->ScratchRSrcReg != AMDGPU::PRIVATE_RSRC_REG && 0
1515 !AMDGPU::SGPR_128RegClass.contains(MFI->ScratchRSrcReg)) { 0
1516 return diagnoseRegisterClass(YamlMFI.ScratchRSrcReg); 0
1517 } ----
1518 ----
1519 if (MFI->FrameOffsetReg != AMDGPU::FP_REG && 0
1520 !AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass.contains(MFI->FrameOffsetReg)) { 0
1521 return diagnoseRegisterClass(YamlMFI.FrameOffsetReg); 0
1522 } ----
1523 ----
1524 if (MFI->StackPtrOffsetReg != AMDGPU::SP_REG && 0
1525 !AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass.contains(MFI->StackPtrOffsetReg)) { 0
1526 return diagnoseRegisterClass(YamlMFI.StackPtrOffsetReg); 0
1527 } ----
1528 ----
1529 for (const auto &YamlReg : YamlMFI.WWMReservedRegs) { 0
1530 Register ParsedReg; 0
1531 if (parseRegister(YamlReg, ParsedReg)) 0
1532 return true; 0
1533 ----
1534 MFI->reserveWWMRegister(ParsedReg); 0
1535 } ----
1536 ----
1537 auto parseAndCheckArgument = [&](const std::optional &A, 0
1538 const TargetRegisterClass &RC, ----
1539 ArgDescriptor &Arg, unsigned UserSGPRs, ----
1540 unsigned SystemSGPRs) { ----
1541 // Skip parsing if it's not present. ----
1542 if (!A) 0
1543 return false; 0
1544 ----
1545 if (A->IsRegister) { 0
1546 Register Reg; 0
1547 if (parseNamedRegisterReference(PFS, Reg, A->RegisterName.Value, Error)) { 0
1548 SourceRange = A->RegisterName.SourceRange; 0
1549 return true; 0
1550 } ----
1551 if (!RC.contains(Reg)) 0
1552 return diagnoseRegisterClass(A->RegisterName); 0
1553 Arg = ArgDescriptor::createRegister(Reg); 0
1554 } else ----
1555 Arg = ArgDescriptor::createStack(A->StackOffset); 0
1556 // Check and apply the optional mask. ----
1557 if (A->Mask) 0
1558 Arg = ArgDescriptor::createArg(Arg, *A->Mask); 0
1559 ----
1560 MFI->NumUserSGPRs += UserSGPRs; 0
1561 MFI->NumSystemSGPRs += SystemSGPRs; 0
1562 return false; 0
1563 }; 0
1564 ----
1565 if (YamlMFI.ArgInfo && 0
1566 (parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->PrivateSegmentBuffer, 0
1567 AMDGPU::SGPR_128RegClass, ----
1568 MFI->ArgInfo.PrivateSegmentBuffer, 4, 0) || 0
1569 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->DispatchPtr, 0
1570 AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, MFI->ArgInfo.DispatchPtr, 0
1571 2, 0) || 0
1572 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->QueuePtr, AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, 0
1573 MFI->ArgInfo.QueuePtr, 2, 0) || 0
1574 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->KernargSegmentPtr, 0
1575 AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, ----
1576 MFI->ArgInfo.KernargSegmentPtr, 2, 0) || 0
1577 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->DispatchID, 0
1578 AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, MFI->ArgInfo.DispatchID, 0
1579 2, 0) || 0
1580 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->FlatScratchInit, 0
1581 AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, ----
1582 MFI->ArgInfo.FlatScratchInit, 2, 0) || 0
1583 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->PrivateSegmentSize, 0
1584 AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass, ----
1585 MFI->ArgInfo.PrivateSegmentSize, 0, 0) || 0
1586 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->LDSKernelId, 0
1587 AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass, ----
1588 MFI->ArgInfo.LDSKernelId, 0, 1) || 0
1589 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->WorkGroupIDX, 0
1590 AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass, MFI->ArgInfo.WorkGroupIDX, 0
1591 0, 1) || 0
1592 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->WorkGroupIDY, 0
1593 AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass, MFI->ArgInfo.WorkGroupIDY, 0
1594 0, 1) || 0
1595 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->WorkGroupIDZ, 0
1596 AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass, MFI->ArgInfo.WorkGroupIDZ, 0
1597 0, 1) || 0
1598 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->WorkGroupInfo, 0
1599 AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass, ----
1600 MFI->ArgInfo.WorkGroupInfo, 0, 1) || 0
1601 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->PrivateSegmentWaveByteOffset, 0
1602 AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass, ----
1603 MFI->ArgInfo.PrivateSegmentWaveByteOffset, 0, 1) || 0
1604 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->ImplicitArgPtr, 0
1605 AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, ----
1606 MFI->ArgInfo.ImplicitArgPtr, 0, 0) || 0
1607 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->ImplicitBufferPtr, 0
1608 AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, ----
1609 MFI->ArgInfo.ImplicitBufferPtr, 2, 0) || 0
1610 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->WorkItemIDX, 0
1611 AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass, ----
1612 MFI->ArgInfo.WorkItemIDX, 0, 0) || 0
1613 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->WorkItemIDY, 0
1614 AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass, ----
1615 MFI->ArgInfo.WorkItemIDY, 0, 0) || 0
1616 parseAndCheckArgument(YamlMFI.ArgInfo->WorkItemIDZ, 0
1617 AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass, ----
1618 MFI->ArgInfo.WorkItemIDZ, 0, 0))) 0
1619 return true; 0
1620 ----
1621 MFI->Mode.IEEE = YamlMFI.Mode.IEEE; 0
1622 MFI->Mode.DX10Clamp = YamlMFI.Mode.DX10Clamp; 0
1623 ----
1624 // FIXME: Move proper support for denormal-fp-math into base MachineFunction ----
1625 MFI->Mode.FP32Denormals.Input = YamlMFI.Mode.FP32InputDenormals 0
1626 ? DenormalMode::IEEE 0
1627 : DenormalMode::PreserveSign; ----

517 return "e-p:32:32-i64:64-v16:16-v24:32-v32:32-v48:64-v96:128" 517 return "e-p:32:32-i64:64-v16:16-v24:32-v32:32-v48:64-v96:128"
518 "-v192:256-v256:256-v512:512-v1024:1024-v2048:2048-n32:64-S32-A5-G1"; 518 "-v192:256-v256:256-v512:512-v1024:1024-v2048:2048-n32:64-S32-A5-G1";
519 } 519 }
520 520
521 // 32-bit private, local, and region pointers. 64-bit global, constant and 521 // 32-bit private, local, and region pointers. 64-bit global, constant and
522 // flat. 160-bit non-integral fat buffer pointers that include a 128-bit 522 // flat. 160-bit non-integral fat buffer pointers that include a 128-bit
523 // buffer descriptor and a 32-bit offset, which are indexed by 32-bit values 523 // buffer descriptor and a 32-bit offset, which are indexed by 32-bit values
524 // (address space 7), and 128-bit non-integral buffer resourcees (address 524 // (address space 7), and 128-bit non-integral buffer resourcees (address

526 // like getelementptr. 526 // like getelementptr.
